      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "id": "278d10c5_4036cb01",
      "file_path": "common-logging/src/main/java/org/onap/policy/common/logging/eelf/PolicyLogger.java",
      "patchset_number": 8,
      "line": 780,
      "message": "Is there a reason why these checks \"enabled\" checks are done in this method but not in the other audit ones?\nThe question will apply to all the other methods, metrics, etc ..",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 477,
        "name": "Jorge Hernandez",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "jorge.hernandez-herrero@att.com",
        "username": "jhh"
      },
      "updated": "2020-04-27 13:46:29.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": null,
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "id": "4ada5316_880fd2f0",
      "file_path": "common-logging/src/main/java/org/onap/policy/common/logging/eelf/PolicyLogger.java",
      "patchset_number": 8,
      "line": 484,
      "message": "So in general with these checks, there's an assumption that if there's only one argument and the it isn't a throwable, the message is the class name. That isn't always going to be the case but if everyone else is okay with that then that is okay with me. It's a small detail.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 1677,
        "name": "Daniel Cruz",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "dc443y@att.com",
        "username": "dc443y"
      },
      "updated": "2020-04-27 13:55:53.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": null,
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "id": "77d93adf_7671ef0e",
      "file_path": "common-logging/src/main/java/org/onap/policy/common/logging/flexlogger/EelfLogger.java",
      "patchset_number": 8,
      "line": 5,
      "message": "License Update",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 1677,
        "name": "Daniel Cruz",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "dc443y@att.com",
        "username": "dc443y"
      },
      "updated": "2020-04-27 13:55:53.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": null,
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "id": "34bec049_1d7a9ca2",
      "file_path": "common-logging/src/main/java/org/onap/policy/common/logging/flexlogger/SystemOutLogger.java",
      "patchset_number": 8,
      "line": 441,
      "message": "Do we really need the check for length of one? Couldn't OnapLoggingUtils.formatMessage() handle the case of only one argument?",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 1677,
        "name": "Daniel Cruz",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "dc443y@att.com",
        "username": "dc443y"
      },
      "updated": "2020-04-27 13:55:53.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": null,
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "id": "8b3bee57_dc806006",
      "file_path": "common-logging/src/main/java/org/onap/policy/common/logging/flexlogger/SystemOutLogger.java",
      "patchset_number": 8,
      "line": 565,
      "message": "What about the arguments?",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 1677,
        "name": "Daniel Cruz",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "dc443y@att.com",
        "username": "dc443y"
      },
      "updated": "2020-04-27 13:55:53.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": null,
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "id": "91b3ed63_34704031",
      "file_path": "common-logging/src/test/java/org/onap/policy/common/logging/flexlogger/EelfLoggerTest.java",
      "patchset_number": 8,
      "line": 6,
      "message": "License Update",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 1677,
        "name": "Daniel Cruz",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "dc443y@att.com",
        "username": "dc443y"
      },
      "updated": "2020-04-27 13:55:53.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": null,
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "id": "30bfbb50_f0af4168",
      "file_path": "common-logging/src/main/java/org/onap/policy/common/logging/eelf/PolicyLogger.java",
      "patchset_number": 8,
      "line": 484,
      "message": "That is certainly what the old method did, the method that this subsumed.  Whether it's a valid assumption or not, I'm not sure.  Honestly, I'm still not sure of the purpose of these changes, as I don't think we intend to modify existing code to use this new functionality.  In fact, I think we plan to eliminate flexlogger altogether.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 811,
        "name": "Jim Hahn",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "jrh3@att.com",
        "username": "jrh3"
      },
      "updated": "2020-04-27 15:18:45.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "4ada5316_880fd2f0",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "id": "d1cb0256_b67d8525",
      "file_path": "common-logging/src/main/java/org/onap/policy/common/logging/flexlogger/SystemOutLogger.java",
      "patchset_number": 8,
      "line": 441,
      "message": "I think SystemOutLogger is the only place where we want to format the message like this - the other loggers still work differently.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 811,
        "name": "Jim Hahn",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "jrh3@att.com",
        "username": "jrh3"
      },
      "updated": "2020-04-27 15:18:45.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "34bec049_1d7a9ca2",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "id": "4cf6fe58_03ee8579",
      "file_path": "common-logging/src/main/java/org/onap/policy/common/logging/flexlogger/SystemOutLogger.java",
      "patchset_number": 8,
      "line": 565,
      "message": "oh, good catch!",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 811,
        "name": "Jim Hahn",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "jrh3@att.com",
        "username": "jrh3"
      },
      "updated": "2020-04-27 15:18:45.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "8b3bee57_dc806006",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "id": "39698f36_cff8a095",
      "file_path": "common-logging/src/main/java/org/onap/policy/common/logging/eelf/PolicyLogger.java",
      "patchset_number": 8,
      "line": 484,
      "message": "I agree that the prior implementation made that assumption but at least it was explicit in the arguments that the string was \"className\" so it gives a hint to the developer of what it is specifically using the string as. I think changing it to message is fine too but then placing the value in the MDC with the classNameProp key is a little off putting to me as it may or may not be an actual class name. That being said I don't have a strong opinion on the matter so I'm fine with it if everyone else is. Perhaps a note in the Java doc that describes under what conditions message is used as a className could help clarify.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 1677,
        "name": "Daniel Cruz",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "dc443y@att.com",
        "username": "dc443y"
      },
      "updated": "2020-04-27 15:33:53.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "30bfbb50_f0af4168",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "id": "473a5029_f5627100",
      "file_path": "common-logging/src/main/java/org/onap/policy/common/logging/eelf/PolicyLogger.java",
      "patchset_number": 8,
      "line": 484,
      "message": "Agreed, the doc on line 477 (and other places) should reflect the fact that this is assumed to be a class name, if there is exactly one argument and the argument is not a throwable.  Wonder how often this is used?",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 811,
        "name": "Jim Hahn",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "jrh3@att.com",
        "username": "jrh3"
      },
      "updated": "2020-04-27 16:08:32.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "39698f36_cff8a095",
      "unresolved": true
    },
